Associate Professor position in artificial intelligence / human system=20
cooperation at IMT Atlantique (https://www.imt-atlantique.fr)

Key words: artificial intelligence, data science, decision aiding,=20
human-system cooperation, human factors.

An Associate Professor position in (F/W) in Artificial Intelligence /=20
Human System Cooperation is open at the IMT Atlantique=20
(https://www.imt-atlantique.fr), Brest campus, in the LUSSI department=20
with a research assignment at the Lab-STICC (UMR CNRS 6285,=20
https://www.labsticc.fr/en/index/) DECIDE team.

IMT Atlantic, the LUSSI department and the DECIDE team offer a pleasant=20
working environment and great opportunities in both research and=20
teaching at the interfaces of data, information and decision sciences.=20
In addition, a particularity of the department is to allow the=20
development of inter-disciplinary collaborations with the humanities and=20
social sciences. The main areas of application are digital, health,=20
energy, environment and the industry of the future.

The priority profile is in artificial intelligence (specifically if=20
possible in data sciences --temporal/streams data--, explainable=20
artificial intelligence and decision support) with a focus on human=20
system cooperation.

For further information and link to application material in English=20
please visit:

https://www.imt-atlantique.fr/en/associate-professor-artificial-intellige=
nce-human-system-cooperatio

Application form & registration conditions:

